# With Terraform Cloud, sensitive variables are NOT stored in this file.
# They are set directly in the TFC workspace UI or via the TFC CLI.
#
# Go to: app.terraform.io → your org → portfolio workspace → Settings → Variables
#
# ── Terraform Variables (set in TFC workspace, mark sensitive ones as "Sensitive") ──
#
#   KEY                     SENSITIVE   VALUE
#   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   aws_region              no          us-east-1
#   environment             no          production
#   project                 no          portfolio
#   ec2_instance_type       no          t3.micro
#   ec2_public_key          YES         <contents of your ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub>
#   allowed_ssh_cidrs       no          ["YOUR.IP.HERE/32"]
#   django_secret_key       YES         <python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))">
#   django_allowed_hosts    no          <EC2-IP>,<your-domain.com>
#   github_repo_url         no          https://github.com/<owner>/portfolio.git
#   frontend_bucket_name    no          portfolio-frontend
#   media_bucket_name       no          portfolio-media
#   cloudfront_price_class  no          PriceClass_100
#   domain_name             no          (leave empty until you have a domain)
#   acm_certificate_arn     no          (leave empty until you have a cert)
#   github_token            YES         <GitHub PAT: repo + admin:repo_hook scopes>
#   github_owner            no          <your GitHub username>
#   github_repo_name        no          portfolio
#
# ── Environment Variables (set in TFC workspace — these auth the AWS provider) ──
#
#   KEY                       SENSITIVE   VALUE
#   ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID         YES         <IAM key for Terraform provisioning user>
#   AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY     YES         <IAM secret>
#   AWS_DEFAULT_REGION        no          us-east-1
#
# ── GitHub Actions Secrets (the ONLY secrets needed in GitHub) ──────────────────
#
#   TF_API_TOKEN        — TFC User or Team API token
#                         Generate at: app.terraform.io → User Settings → Tokens
#
#   (All app deployment secrets are still needed in GitHub for deploy-app.yml:
#    AWS_ROLE_ARN, AWS_REGION, S3_BUCKET_FRONTEND, S3_BUCKET_MEDIA,
#    CLOUDFRONT_DISTRIBUTION_ID, CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN, EC2_HOST,
#    EC2_SSH_KEY, DJANGO_SECRET_KEY)
#
# ── This file is intentionally NOT a working tfvars file ────────────────────────
# There is nothing to copy here. All variables are managed in TFC.
# This file serves as documentation only.
